-- PRESS DIGEST - RUSSIA - May 14
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 05:07AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, May 14 (Reuters) - The following are some of the leading stories in Russia's newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

VEDOMOSTI www.vedomosti.ru - The Russian Economy Ministry expects total economic growth of 9.6 percent in Russia in 2013-2017, compared to 19.8 percent seen for the global economy, the daily writes. - Russian credit card holders owed banks more than one trillion roubles ($28.72 billion) in the first quarter of 2014, the daily writes. - The volume of bank deposits shrunk by almost 400 billion roubles ($11.49 billion) in the first quarter of 2014, the daily writes citing official data.  KOMMERSANT www.kommersant.ru - Sales of cars in Russia dropped 8 percent in January-April 2014 year-on-year due to weakening rouble, the paper writes. - Economy Minister Alexei Ulyukayev said Russia would spend 112 billion roubles ($3.22 billion) in Crimea and that the money will be taken away from projects including a bridge over the Lena river in Siberia and a port in the southern Krasnodar region, the daily writes.